body:
I see there seems to be a popular issue with ping spikes and fps jumps during this patch cycle. 
I thought it might be my rig or my ISP giving me the short end of the bandwidth but my connectivity is above average for the region, and during game play i don't have any other CPU consuming processes running.
However, when there is a lot of player activity (Like a 5v5 exchange) ping spikes and fps issues seem to swarm my comp, and no matter how low i set the graphics these issues don't subside. {{sticker:zombie-brand-mindblown}}
